node.text:
Mont-Saint-Michel, France 😍 Who would you want to visit with?

It has the distinction of being erected on a rocky tidal island, surrounded by a magnificent bay. The Mount and its bay are listed as World Heritage by UNESCO. This grandiose spot, located 3 and a half hours from Paris, is one of the most famous and visited landmark in France.

📽 @_pifou #nature
📍 Mont-Saint-Michel, Normandy, France

node.text:
Holding a baby one to the biggest one via @thereptilezoo. An Aldabra tortoise weighing 672 pounds (305 kilograms) is the world's largest free-roaming tortoise ever recorded. They are found on Aldabra Island, one of the Seychelles northeast of Madagascar in the Indian Ocean. They were apparently introduced to Mauritius and Reunion Islands.

Lifespan is around 120 years, however there’s is a male by the name of Jonathan which hatched in 1832, and is the oldest known living land animal at 189 years of age. Before Johnathan another male by the name of Adwaita held that record at 206 years of age, unfortunately he died in 2006.

📽 @thereptilezoo #nature
